Description: Fragment of round handle and shoulder of a Lesbian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine, micaceous, orange-red. Graffito on face of handle.
Curator's comments: A Lesbian red-ware amphora. If the reading of the graffito is NI the script suggests a date earlier than c.550. Trimmed. Probably excavated by Petrie, not brought in to him.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JA.052)
